name: Nuggets vs Timberwolves
summary: The Denver Nuggets and Minnesota Timberwolves are tied 2-2 in their NBA playoff series. The two teams will face off in Game 4 on Friday, April 22nd. The Nuggets are favored to win the game, with odds of -3.5. The Timberwolves are +3.5 underdogs. The game will be played at the Target Center in Minneapolis, Minnesota. It will start at 9:30 p.m. ET and will be televised on TNT. The Nuggets won Game 3 by a score of 115-107. Nikola Jokic led the way for the Nuggets with 30 points, 18 rebounds, and 10 assists. Karl-Anthony Towns led the way for the Timberwolves with 28 points and 12 rebounds. The Nuggets are now 2-0 at home in the series. The Timberwolves are 2-0 at home. The winner of Game 4 will take a 3-2 lead in the series.
